This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it focuses on using social network data to select peer change agents for HIV prevention. It could also belong to the sub-category of Computational Biology (cs.CY) as it deals with HIV prevention and treatment. Additionally, it could be classified under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SD) and Systems and Humans (cs.SY) as it involves developing an AI algorithm to select and train peer leaders. Finally, it could also be classified under the sub-category of Computers and Society (cs.CE) as it deals with a social issue and the use of technology to address it.
